OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,386,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F385A1781583452
OL,3,CTwo cygnets die after being struck
OL,4,Cduring regatta race
OL,6,FIn a statement, the Organising
OL,7,FCommittee of Reading Amateur Regatta
OL,8,Fsaid: "The team behind Reading Amateur
OL,9,FRegatta are deeply saddened that two
OL,10,Fcygnets died following a collision
OL,11,Fwith one of the racing boats at the
OL,12,Fend of the first day of this year's
OL,13,Fevent.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,386,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F385A1781583452
OL,3,CTwo cygnets die after being struck
OL,4,Cduring regatta race
OL,6,F"Significant planning and a range of
OL,7,Fmeasures, developed with advice from
OL,8,FSwan Support, were put in place before
OL,9,Fthe event to protect wildlife. These
OL,10,Fmeasures included using launches to
OL,11,Fencourage waterfowl away from the
OL,12,Fracing lane, using a range of
OL,13,Fcommunication channels to ask
OL,14,Fspectators not to feed birds along the
OL,15,Fcourse, relocating wildfowl considered
OL,16,Fto be at risk to designated holding
OL,17,Fareas, and stopping races where an
OL,18,Fimmediate risk of collision with
OL,19,Fwildlife was identified.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,386,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F385A1781583452
OL,3,CTwo cygnets die after being struck
OL,4,Cduring regatta race
OL,6,F"Swan Support were present on both
OL,7,Fdays and actively provided valuable
OL,8,Fsupport. Additional measures were put
OL,9,Fin place on the second day.
OL,11,F"We deeply regret that, despite these
OL,12,Fefforts, this incident occurred. We
OL,13,Fare working closely with Swan Support,
OL,14,FBritish Rowing and the Environment
OL,15,FAgency to understand exactly what
OL,16,Fhappened, identify any lessons that
OL,17,Fcan be learned, and consider what
OL,18,Ffurther measures may be appropriate in
OL,19,Fthe future."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
